      • fromConfig

        public static HyperParamValues<?> fromConfig(com.typesafe.config.Config config,
                             String key)
        Parameters:
        config - application configuration
        key - config key to access
        Returns:
        a HyperParamValues appropriate to the value. If an int or double, returns fixed(int) or fixed(double) respectively. If a List<int> or List<double>, returns range(int,int) or range(double,double) respectively.

      • chooseHyperParameterCombos

        public static List<List<?>> chooseHyperParameterCombos(Collection<HyperParamValues<?>> ranges,
                                       int howMany,
                                       int perParam)
        Parameters:
        ranges - ranges of hyperparameters to try, one per hyperparameters
        howMany - how many combinations of hyperparameters to return
        perParam - how many different hyperparameter values to try per hyperparameter
        Returns:
        combinations of concrete hyperparameter values. For example, for 5 parameters each with 3 values to try, the total number of combinations returned could be up to pow(3,5) or 243. The number could be less if the ranges do not actually have that many distinct values. If howMany is smaller than the total number of combinations, a random subset of all combinations are returned. The order is shuffled randomly. If no parameters are specified or perParam is 0, a single empty combination is returned.

      • chooseValuesPerHyperParam

        public static int chooseValuesPerHyperParam(int numParams,
                            int candidates)
        Parameters:
        numParams - number of different hyperparameters
        candidates - minimum number of candidates to be built
        Returns:
        smallest value such that pow(value, numParams) is at least the number of candidates requested to build. Returns 0 if numParams is less than 1.
